{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md | sed -n '60,90p'\"","aggregated_output":"    60\tAudit findings:\n    61\t- host-side insights fallback already reads a persisted usage report from `~/.codex/codex_managed_agent_usage_report.json`\n    62\t- webview UI state persists topic-driven navigation state through `vscode.setState()`\n    63\t- first bounded reliability gap: persisted `topicFocus` is not revalidated against current insights data or current threads after reload\n    64\t- host-side persisted-report fallback is sufficient for webview reload recovery; a second reload-survivable webview cache would be redundant right now\n    65\t\n    66\tCompleted in this milestone:\n    67\t- persisted `topicFocus` is now cleared on reload when current thread data no longer supports the saved insight navigation state\n    68\t- active-session insights rendering now reuses the last usable report payload when a transient refresh arrives empty\n    69\t- insights UI now explicitly discloses when it is showing persisted fallback data or an in-session cached report\n    70\t- insights disclosure now includes a freshness timestamp for persisted fallback data and in-session cached reports\n    71\t\n    72\tCurrent bounded slice:\n    73\t- add explicit stale wording when persisted fallback insights are older than a simple threshold\n    74\t\n    75\t### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\n    76\tStatus: pending\n    77\t\n    78\tTargets:\n    79\t- background continue observability\n    80\t- clear loop status semantics\n    81\t- degraded-state handling\n    82\t- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n    83\t\n    84\t### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\n    85\tStatus: pending\n    86\t\n    87\tTargets:\n    88\t- release workflow\n    89\t- screenshots / notes / docs\n    90\t- smoke validation routine\n","exit_code":0,"status"